  "assumptions": [
    "The execution-facing artifact intentionally stops before concrete LP emission; it specifies what an emitter must instantiate, not the final emitted file.",
    "The lower-bound phase models rounds 1 through 12 because Appendix A.1 derives the 24-round claim from a 12-round lower bound and applies it to two consecutive windows.",
    "For the 12-round lower-bound unit, round keys K1 through K12 are required; this means key-schedule updates 1 through 11 are modeled, while the update after round 12 is omitted because K13 is unused in this unit.",
    "The PRESENT S-box is bijective with branch number 2, so Eq. (5) is omitted in this instantiation because Sect. 2.2 says it is redundant in that case.",
    "XORing the round counter constant into key-register bits k19..k15 does not change XOR-difference bits, so the difference model may copy the post-S-box key-register state into the next-round key register."
  ],
  "variable_families": [
    {
      "family_id": "state_pre_round",
      "variable_kind": "difference_bit",
      "binary": true,
      "naming_pattern": "s_r{round}_b{bit}",
